{
  "name": "Divine Word",
  "_id": "matSplDivineWord",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You utter a word imbued with power from the Upper Planes. Each creature of your choice in range makes a Charisma saving throw. On a failed save, a target that has 50 Hit Points or fewer suffers an effect based on its current Hit Points, as shown in the Divine Word Effects table. Regardless of its Hit Points, an Aberration, Celestial, Elemental, Fey, or Fiend target that fails its save is forced back to its plane of origin (if it isn't there already) and can't return to the current plane for 24 hours by any means short of a <em>@UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.matSplWish000000]{Wish}</em> spell.</p><table><thead><tr><td>Hit Points</td><td>Divine Word Effect</td></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>0-20</td><td>The target dies.</td></tr><tr><td>21-30</td><td>The target has the &amp;Reference[Blinded apply=false], &amp;Reference[Deafened apply=false], and &amp;Reference[Stunned apply=false] conditions for 1 hour.</td></tr><tr><td>31040</td><td>The target has the Blinded and Deafened conditions for 10 minutes.</td></tr><tr><td>41-50</td><td>The target has the Deafened condition for 1 minute.</td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong>Using a Higher-Level Spell Slot.</strong>The range increases by 30 feet for each spell slot level above 7.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
